    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - ASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Inspect the O-rings and replace if necessary.</para>
        <para>Apply Eaton Lubricant #71214 supplied with the O-ring kit to the auxiliary drive gear O-rings.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the front auxiliary drive gear on a clean, flat surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017d7">Figure 137</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017d7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017d7" filename="../figg13/G13017d7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 137. Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the O-rings on the front auxiliary drive gear hub (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017d7">Figure 137</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining ring on the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017d8">Figure 138</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017d8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017d8" filename="../figg13/G13017d8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 138. Retaining Ring on Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017d9">Figure 139</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017d9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017d9" filename="../figg13/G13017d9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 139. Install Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring in the gear hub groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e0">Figure 140</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017e0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017e0" filename="../figg13/G13017e0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 140. Snap Ring In Gear Hub Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver to install the outer retainer ring.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
